b. mare inferam. The sea on the west coast of Italy, from Liguria to Sicily, was called by the Greeks mare Tyrrhenum. The common Roman name was mare Inferum, distinguishing it from the upper sea, mare Superum, the Hadriatie, on the eastern side.
